reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Gives us additional charging options
reviews.reviewText: We use this in both of our trucks for faster charging. Our phones are USB-C and this just adds another option for fast charging. No issues with it so far.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This is the efficiency needed for travel
reviews.reviewText: This is a great adapter. The cord is high quality braided nylon and doesn't have the unsightly bends in it from being folded in the packaging. It doesn't really fast charge but whose in their car that long anyways?

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars 65W USB C Output/30W USB A Output Small/Metal Car Charger
reviews.reviewText: Much smaller than other car chargers with a 65W USB C output. Very solid metal housing, tested charging a Samsung Galaxy Book 360 and with a USB meter - works fine. The cable that came with the charger is much thinner than the other high wattage rated cables I have (1 meter/40 inches long with a braided fabric wrapper.) The price of this charger is also significantly lower than other chargers with a 65W output.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Works great and seams to be well made. Time will tell as I am very hard on car chargers.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars USB-C with fast charging speed!
reviews.reviewText: I bought this to keep in the car for my OnePlus 9, which charges incredibly fast when using a proper cable and power supply. Using AccuBattery app, the OEM charger usually peaks around 40W, to charge the phone in about 40 min. Most "fast chargers" that I've used have come nowhere close to this, usually peaking around 20W. I am happy to report that this charger in the car typically hits in the high 30's W, charging my phone incredibly fast.I haven't tested with other devices, though I'd be interested to do more tests with other devices, such as my wife's iPhone, Steam Deck, Laptop, etc.Very pleased with this charger, I'm buying another to keep in the other car. Great charger, great price, I'm happy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works Perfectly As Advertised!
reviews.reviewText: Works perfectly as advertised. Not 100% flush but I am using a very small cigarette lighter that has a sliding cover to conceal. The sliding cover has no problem going over the charger which is in a very tight space. VERY HAPPY

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars WAY too long
reviews.reviewText: I bought this because I wanted a FLUSH fitting adapter, NOT one that sticks out 1/2” or more. I bought two of these. These are WAY too long for both my 2002 Chevy truck and my 2020 Volvo. So, for both old American and New European they are just too long. Why advertise these as flush fit when they are too long for most standard 12v outlets? As info, for those who care, this is well over 2" long and you'll want one that is about 1.7" long if you TRULY want a flush fit. These shorter ones are available on Amazon, like the ones I just bought to replace these (Amazon ASIN B0BBZ64F1C) that I am returning - just make sure to double check the length before you buy!
